import requests
import json
import geopandas as gpd
import getpass

# Load & Simplify Philly Boundary

philly_geojson_path = "/workspaces/04-vegetation-charliewrede/City_Limits.geojson"

philly_gdf = gpd.read_file(philly_geojson_path)
philly_gdf = philly_gdf.to_crs(epsg=4326)

# Dissolve into one city polygon
philly_union = philly_gdf.dissolve()

# Simplify geometry 
philly_union["geometry"] = philly_union.simplify(tolerance=0.001)

# Convert to GeoJSON for API
geojson = json.loads(philly_union.to_json())

# Authenticate with AppEEARS

username = input("Earthdata Username: ")
password = getpass.getpass("Earthdata Password: ")

login_response = requests.post(
    "https://appeears.earthdatacloud.nasa.gov/api/login",
    auth=(username, password)
)

if login_response.status_code != 200:
    print("Login failed:", login_response.text)
    exit()

print("Login successful!")

token = login_response.json()["token"]

headers = {
    "Authorization": f"Bearer {token}"
}

# 3. Fast One-Year GeoTIFF NDVI Task

task = {
    "task_type": "area",
    "task_name": "Philadelphia_NDVI_FAST_2021",
    "params": {
        "dates": [
            {
                "startDate": "07-01-2021",
                "endDate": "07-31-2021" 
            }
        ],
        "layers": [
            {
                "product": "MOD13Q1.061",
                "layer": "_250m_16_days_NDVI"
            }
        ],
        "geo": geojson,
        "output": {
            "format": {
                "type": "geotiff"  
            },
            "projection": "geographic"
        }
    }
}

task_response = requests.post(
    "https://appeears.earthdatacloud.nasa.gov/api/task",
    headers=headers,
    json=task
)

print("Task response:")
print(task_response.json())

if "task_id" in task_response.json():
    task_id = task_response.json()["task_id"]
    print("Task successfully created!")
    print("FAST GeoTIFF Task ID:", task_id)
else:
    print("Task failed or no task_id returned")

import os
import glob
import json
import requests

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
import rioxarray as rxr
import xarray as xr
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.colors import to_rgb
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1.inset_locator import inset_axes

from shapely.geometry import mapping
from scipy.stats import pearsonr
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Census Tracts
# Found this at https://opendataphilly.org/datasets/census-tracts/ 
tract_path = "/workspaces/04-vegetation-charliewrede/Census_Tracts_2010.geojson"

tracts = gpd.read_file(tract_path)
tracts = tracts[(tracts["STATEFP10"] == "42") & (tracts["COUNTYFP10"] == "101")].copy()
tracts = tracts.to_crs(epsg=4326)
tracts["GEOID10"] = tracts["GEOID10"].astype(str)


# Download 2020 census race data via API

base_url = "https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl"
params = {
    "get": "NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_006N,P2_002N",
    # total_pop, white, black, asian, hispanic
    "for": "tract:*",
    "in": "state:42 county:101"
}

resp = requests.get(base_url, params=params)
resp.raise_for_status()

data = resp.json()
header = data[0]
rows = data[1:]
race_df = pd.DataFrame(rows, columns=header)

# Convert numeric fields
for col in ["P1_001N", "P1_003N", "P1_004N", "P1_006N", "P2_002N"]:
    race_df[col] = pd.to_numeric(race_df[col], errors="coerce")

race_df["GEOID10"] = race_df["state"] + race_df["county"] + race_df["tract"]

race_df = race_df.rename(columns={
    "P1_001N": "total_pop",
    "P1_003N": "white",
    "P1_004N": "black",
    "P1_006N": "asian",
    "P2_002N": "hispanic"  
})

# compute percentages
race_df["white_pct"] = race_df["white"] / race_df["total_pop"] * 100
race_df["black_pct"] = race_df["black"] / race_df["total_pop"] * 100
race_df["asian_pct"] = race_df["asian"] / race_df["total_pop"] * 100
race_df["hispanic_pct"] = race_df["hispanic"] / race_df["total_pop"] * 100


# Merge race and tracts

tracts_race = tracts.merge(
    race_df[[
        "GEOID10", "NAME", "total_pop",
        "white", "black", "asian", "hispanic",
        "white_pct", "black_pct", "asian_pct", "hispanic_pct"
    ]],
    on="GEOID10",
    how="left"
)


# NDVI rasters

ndvi_dir = "/workspaces/04-vegetation-charliewrede"
ndvi_files = sorted(glob.glob(os.path.join(ndvi_dir, "MOD13Q1.061__250m_16_days_NDVI_doy*.tif")))


ndvi_das = []
for f in ndvi_files:
    fname = os.path.basename(f)
    doy_pos = fname.find("doy") + 3
    doy_str = fname[doy_pos:doy_pos+7]

    year = int(doy_str[:4])
    doy = int(doy_str[4:])
    date = pd.to_datetime(f"{year}-{doy}", format="%Y-%j")

    da = rxr.open_rasterio(f)
    if "band" in da.dims:
        da = da.squeeze("band")

    da = da.astype("float32")
    da = da.where(da > -3000) / 10000.0
    da = da.assign_coords(date=date).expand_dims("date")
    da.name = "NDVI"
    ndvi_das.append(da)

ndvi_ts = xr.concat(ndvi_das, dim="date").sortby("date")

if not ndvi_ts.rio.crs:
    ndvi_ts = ndvi_ts.rio.write_crs("EPSG:4326")

ndvi_mean_time = ndvi_ts.mean(dim="date")
ndvi_mean_time.name = "NDVI_mean"

# zonal statistics

tracts_race = tracts_race.to_crs(ndvi_ts.rio.crs)

vals = []

for idx, row in tracts_race.iterrows():
    try:
        clipped = ndvi_mean_time.rio.clip([row.geometry], tracts_race.crs)
        vals.append(float(clipped.mean().values))
    except:
        vals.append(np.nan)

tracts_race["mean_ndvi"] = vals

# Majority

majority_white   = tracts_race[tracts_race["white_pct"]   >= 50]
majority_black   = tracts_race[tracts_race["black_pct"]   >= 50]
majority_asian   = tracts_race[tracts_race["asian_pct"]   >= 50]
majority_latino  = tracts_race[tracts_race["hispanic_pct"] >= 50]

print("\nGroup counts:")
print("Majority white:",  len(majority_white))
print("Majority black:",  len(majority_black))
print("Majority asian:",  len(majority_asian))
print("Majority latino:", len(majority_latino))

# 7. Correlation and scatterplot

def add_regression_line(ax, x, y):
    X = np.array(x).reshape(-1, 1)
    model = LinearRegression().fit(X, y)
    x_line = np.linspace(min(x), max(x), 200)
    y_line = model.predict(x_line.reshape(-1, 1))
    ax.plot(x_line, y_line, color="red", linewidth=2, label="Trend line")


def scatter(x_col, label):
    common = tracts_race.dropna(subset=[x_col, "mean_ndvi"])
    r, p = pearsonr(common[x_col], common["mean_ndvi"])
    print(f"\nCorrelation NDVI vs {label}: r={r:.3f}, p={p:.4f}")

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.scatter(common[x_col], common["mean_ndvi"], alpha=0.6, label="Census Tracts")
    add_regression_line(ax, common[x_col], common["mean_ndvi"])
    ax.set_xlabel(label)
    ax.set_ylabel("Mean NDVI")
    ax.set_title(f"NDVI vs {label} (r = {r:.3f})")
    ax.legend()
    plt.grid(alpha=0.3)
    plt.show()


# run the scatter plots
scatter("white_pct",   "% White")
scatter("black_pct",   "% Black")
scatter("asian_pct",   "% Asian")
scatter("hispanic_pct","% Latino/Hispanic")

#  Defined a bivariate color scheme (3x3 matrix)

bivariate_colors = {
    (0, 0): "#e8e8e8",
    (0, 1): "#b5c0da",
    (0, 2): "#6c83b5",
    (1, 0): "#cbb8d7",
    (1, 1): "#9a86b1",
    (1, 2): "#634689",
    (2, 0): "#c4a7c6",
    (2, 1): "#8c5983",
    (2, 2): "#552d58"
}

# Function to create bivariate maps

from matplotlib.colors import to_rgb
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1.inset_locator import inset_axes

def make_bivariate_map(df, race_col, output_title):

    working = df.dropna(subset=[race_col, "mean_ndvi"]).copy()

    # Bin variables into 3 quantile classes
    working["race_bin"] = pd.qcut(working[race_col], q=3, labels=[0, 1, 2])
    working["ndvi_bin"] = pd.qcut(working["mean_ndvi"], q=3, labels=[0, 1, 2])

    # Assign combined bivariate color
    working["bivar_color"] = working.apply(
        lambda r: bivariate_colors[(int(r["ndvi_bin"]), int(r["race_bin"]))], axis=1
    )

    # Create map 
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 10))
    working.plot(color=working["bivar_color"], ax=ax, edgecolor="black", linewidth=0.3)

    ax.set_title(output_title, fontsize=18)
    ax.axis("off")

    #  Add legend on the lower right
    # width/height can be changed; loc="lower right" places it along lower right of the map
    legend_ax = inset_axes(ax, width="22%", height="22%", loc="lower right", borderpad=2)

    matrix_rgb = np.array([
        [to_rgb(bivariate_colors[(2,0)]), to_rgb(bivariate_colors[(2,1)]), to_rgb(bivariate_colors[(2,2)])],
        [to_rgb(bivariate_colors[(1,0)]), to_rgb(bivariate_colors[(1,1)]), to_rgb(bivariate_colors[(1,2)])],
        [to_rgb(bivariate_colors[(0,0)]), to_rgb(bivariate_colors[(0,1)]), to_rgb(bivariate_colors[(0,2)])],
    ])

    legend_ax.imshow(matrix_rgb)

    legend_ax.set_xticks([0, 1, 2])
    legend_ax.set_yticks([0, 1, 2])
    legend_ax.set_xticklabels(["Low", "Med", "High"])
    legend_ax.set_yticklabels(["High", "Med", "Low"])  # NDVI increases upward

    legend_ax.set_xlabel(f"{race_col} (%) ", fontsize=8)
    legend_ax.set_ylabel(" NDVI", fontsize=8)
    legend_ax.set_title("Bivariate Legend", fontsize=9)

    plt.show()



# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 3) Run the maps for each group
# ---------------------------------------------------------

make_bivariate_map(tracts_race, "white_pct", "White Population % vs NDVI")
make_bivariate_map(tracts_race, "black_pct", "Black Population % vs NDVI")
make_bivariate_map(tracts_race, "asian_pct", "Asian Population % vs NDVI")
make_bivariate_map(tracts_race, "hispanic_pct", "Latino/Hispanic % vs NDVI")
